# Exclude standalone container services from the Vercel build context. These run
# separately (Fly/Render/local or opt-in paid Vercel), not as part of this
# project's Next.js deploy. Their Dockerfiles are also named plain `Dockerfile`
# (not `Dockerfile.vercel`) so Vercel's Functions auto-detection doesn't try to
# provision them, which was timing out on the free plan.
#
# Patterns are root-anchored (leading slash) so they only match the top-level
# service directories and NOT app code like src/lib/directus/.
/backend/
/directus/
